text:
Grand Concourse (left), south from near E. 156th Street, as seen from the lower end of Franz Siegel Park. In the left background are discernible the Hell Gate and Triborough Bridges.

View 1: July 7, 1936
View 2: June 9, 1940

P. L. Sperr

title: Bronx: Grand Concourse - 156th Street (East)

text:
(1)
Grand Concourse (Mott Ave.), south from and including East 156th Street, to (No. 700) but not including East 153rd Street, showing construction work in progress on new apartment houses.

April 30, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A closer view of part of the same. Also seen is a general view eastward across the Melrose yard of the New York Central Railroad.

April 30, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same as view 1, viewed from the opposite direction (northward). The 6-story apartment house, on the left, is the Alexandria, bearing No. 760, at the N.E. corner of East 156th Street.

April 30, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
